You are a senior full-stack engineer. Build a complete production-ready MVP for a **Real Estate 360° Virtual Tour Platform** inspired by automotive virtual showrooms like Kia VR Showroom.

## 🎯 Goal

Create a full-stack web application where:

* Sellers can upload 360° room images and create property listings
* Buyers can explore properties using an interactive 360° viewer with hotspots and room navigation
* The system supports a hybrid experience:

  * Intro video (external, e.g., Google Earth Studio)
  * Interactive 360° virtual tour (main feature)

---

## 🏗️ Tech Stack Requirements

### Frontend

* React (Vite)
* Tailwind CSS
* 360 Viewer: Pannellum (MVP), structured for future migration to Three.js
* Axios for API calls

### Backend

* Node.js + Express
* MongoDB (Mongoose)

### Storage

* Cloudinary (for image uploads)

---

## 📦 Features to Implement

### 1. Seller Features

* Create property listing (title, address, price)
* Add rooms to listing
* Upload 360° panoramic images per room
* Add hotspots:

  * navigation hotspots (link rooms)
  * feature hotspots (text description)

---

### 2. Buyer Features

* View property tour
* Navigate rooms via:

  * hotspots
  * room selector (thumbnails)
* Smooth transitions between rooms
* Display hotspot tooltips

---

### 3. Core Viewer Features

* 360° panorama rendering using Pannellum
* Hotspot rendering with:

  * yaw
  * pitch
* Scene switching (room-to-room navigation)

---

## 🧩 Database Schema

### Listing

* id
* title
* address
* price
* rooms (array of Room IDs)

### Room

* id
* name
* imageUrl
* listingId
* hotspots (array)

### Hotspot

* id
* type ("navigation" | "feature")
* yaw
* pitch
* targetRoomId (for navigation)
* text
* description

